  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Comparing Fourier Optics and Contrast Transfer Function Modeling of Image Formation in Low Energy Electron Microscopy</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-27</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">• Compares Fourier optics (FO) and contrast transfer function (CTF) for low energy electron microscopy (LEEM). • Compares FO and CTF simulations to experimental defocus series for rippled, suspended graphene. • Temporal and spatial coherence and spherical aberrations produce differences between CTF and FO. • Strong phase and defocus may undermine the validity of the CTF approach for LEEM. • Guides the use of FO and CTF for LEEM and lays the foundation for quantitative image analysis.</subfield>
